<TITLE> SC upholds freeze on Tarique tax-dodge case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 28 (bdnews24.com)  The Supreme Court Thursday upheld a High Court order that halted the proceedings of the tax-dodge case against BNP senior joint secretary general Tarique Rahman. The five-strong bench of the Appellate Division led by chief justice MM Ruhul Amin passed the order on the appeal filed by the National Board of Revenue. The Appellate Division ordered the defence and the prosecution to make arrangements to dispose of the writ petition pending trial in the High Court. Advocate MR Hassan stood for NBR while barrister Rafique-ul-Huq represented Tarique in the court. The High Court on Aug 12 stayed the tax evasion case proceedings for three months on a writ petition. The court has given the NBR chairman and Dhaka special judge six weeks to explain why the case would not be declared illegal . The NBR filed the case against Tarique with Dhaka Special Judge's Court on Aug 4 last year. The BNP leader allegedly dodged taxes worth Tk 26.86 lakh from 2002-03 to 2005-06 tax sessions, the case details stated. bd
